OL,3,C'Everything costs more', Muslims mark
OL,4,CRamadan amid rising bills and food
OL,5,Cprices
OL,7,FA food store at the heart of Bristol's
OL,8,FEaston community is usually bustling
OL,9,Fduring Ramadan.
OL,11,FShelves are packed with dates, spices
OL,12,Fand cuts of lamb, staples for the holy
OL,13,Fmonth. These items are normally in
OL,14,Fhigh demand as families prepare to
OL,15,Fbreak their fast at sunset.
OL,17,FShop owner of Masalaa Baazar, Sakib,
OL,18,Fsays while customers are still coming
OL,19,Fthrough the door, they are spending
OL,20,Ffar less as the UK's cost of living
OL,21,Fcrisis continues to bite.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
